
                   <p style="text-align: center">
                       <b>Title:</b> Steps
1. Sign in to the Grid Manager from the primary Admin Node on either grid.
2. Select CONFIGURATION > System > Grid federation.
3. Select Add connection.
4. Enter details for the connection.<br>
                       <b>Bounding box:</b> x1=184, y1=498, x2=1566, y2=1880
                   </p>
                   <div align="center"><table border="1" class="dataframe">
  <thead>
    <tr style="text-align: right;">
      <th></th>
      <th>0</th>
      <th>1</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th>0</th>
      <td>Field</td>
      <td>Description</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>1</th>
      <td>Connection name</td>
      <td>A unique name to help you recognize this connection, for example,\n"Grid 1-Grid 2."</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>FQDN or IP for this grid</td>
      <td>One of the following:\n• The FQDN of the grid you are currently signed into\n• A VIP address of an HA group on this grid\n• An IP address of an Admin Node or Gateway Node on this grid.\nThe IP can be on any network that the destination grid can reach.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>Port</td>
      <td>The port you want to use for this connection. You can enter any\nunused port number from 23000 to 23999.\nBoth grids in this connection will use the same port. You must ensure\nthat no node in either grid uses this port for other connections.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>4</th>
      <td>Certificate valid days for this grid</td>
      <td>The number of days you want the security certificates for this grid in\nthe connection to be valid. The default value is 730 days (2 years),\nbut you can enter any value from 1 to 762 days.\nStorageGRID automatically generates client and server certificates for\neach grid when you save the connection.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>5</th>
      <td>Provisioning passphrase for this\ngrid</td>
      <td>The provisioning passphrase for the grid you are signed in to.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>6</th>
      <td>FQDN or IP for the other grid</td>
      <td>One of the following:\n• The FQDN of the grid you want to connect to\n• A VIP address of an HA group on the other grid\n• An IP address of an Admin Node or Gateway Node on the other\ngrid. The IP can be on any network that the source grid can reach.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table></div>
